  "gapRefinements": [
    "Endpoint/cloud v1 and v2 existed in the same load path without explicit precedence; v2 is now primary and v1 is legacy compatibility.",
    "Packs used cybersecurity as a content domain while the runtime key is cyber; canonical runtimeDomainKey=cyber is now added across all packs.",
    "Safety posture needed explicit Marion/Mac protective constraints: no covert monitoring, no autonomous enforcement, no punitive action, and explicit confirmation for sensitive actions.",
    "Incident response lacked a critical severity tier in the visible framework; critical containment guidance has been added.",
    "Identity/access now explicitly states that voice identity, liveness, and continuity are evidence only, never authority.",
    "Security culture now includes behavior anticipation without profiling, covert surveillance, or punitive interpretation.",
    "Source ladder now includes a high-stakes source-use protocol to avoid stale/current guidance drift.",
